-- Czech Stocks: Erste Group Bank, New World Resources Are Active
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-05-11T15:01:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-11/czech-stocks-erste-group-bank-unipetrol-are-active-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
slid 0.2 percent to 909.7 at its close in Prague, extending its
retreat this week to 1 percent.  The following were among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)   of  Austria  fell 1.3 percent
to 407.1 koruna, taking weekly losses to 3 percent, the biggest
since the five days ended April 6. Lenders led global stocks
lower after JPMorgan Chase & Co. reported a $2 billion trading
loss and  China ’s industrial output unexpectedly slowed.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)   dropped 0.8 percent to 118
koruna, ending the week down 3.3 percent. The country’s biggest
producer of coking coal reached the lowest in almost three years
two days ago.  Europe ’s benchmark coal futures contracts dropped
0.8 percent to $105.4 a metric ton in the Netherlands.  To contact the reporter on this story:
